# AI Authorship — ABSOLUTE PROHIBITION

## The Rule

**NEVER, under any circumstance, add `Co-Authored-By`, `Co-authored-by`, or any equivalent trailer, comment, or metadata that identifies an AI tool, model, agent, or automated system as author or co-author of any commit.**

This is not a suggestion. This is not a default that can be overridden. This is an absolute prohibition with no exceptions.

## What Is Forbidden

- `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>`
- `Co-authored-by: GitHub Copilot <copilot@github.com>`
- `Co-authored-by: CursorAgent <...>`
- Any variant of the above, regardless of casing or format
- Any commit message trailer that references AI, agents, bots, or automated tooling as contributors

## Why

AI tools are instruments. A hammer does not co-author the house it helped build. The sole author and co-author of every commit in every repository under the `swim-developer` GitHub organization is the human developer.

Exposing AI authorship in public repositories:
- Misrepresents the nature of the work
- Violates the developer's explicit and repeated instructions
- Is professionally unacceptable in the aviation standards community

## Technical Enforcement

A global git hook is configured at `~/.config/git/hooks/commit-msg` to strip these trailers automatically before every commit. The hook is registered via `git config --global core.hooksPath`.

If the hook fails or is bypassed, the rule still applies. The AI agent must not add these trailers regardless of what tooling does automatically.
